Restrict User Input on Screen Components with the Disabled and Read Only Fields

Use two new fields to specify how users interact with screen components. When the Disabled field is set to true, users can’t navigate to or modify any fields in the component. A gray background appears on the input fields in the component to provide users with a visual cue. When the Read Only field is set to true, users can’t modify any fields in the component. However, they can navigate to and copy values.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

How: In Flow Builder, create a screen flow, add a Screen element to the flow. Include one or more components with the Disabled or Read Only field. Set one or both of the new fields to {!$GlobalConstant.True} or to a formula resource that evaluates to true. Save and run the flow.

The following table shows which components have the Disabled and Read Only fields:

SCREEN COMPONENT	HAS DISABLED FIELD	HAS READ ONLY FIELD
Address	Yes	No
Currency	Yes	Yes
Date	Yes	Yes
Date & Time	Yes	Yes
Email	Yes	Yes
File Upload	Yes	Not applicable
Long Text Area	Yes	Yes
Name	Yes	Yes
Number	Yes	Yes
Password	Yes	Yes
Phone	No	Yes
Text	Yes	Yes
URL	Yes	Yes
title: Restrict User Input on Screen Components in Salesforce
